entries.title: New York Times: White House chief of staff Ron Klain expected to step down
entries.description: White House chief of staff Ron Klain is expected to step down from his role in the coming weeks, The New York Times reported Saturday.

entries.title: 'Avengers' star Jeremy Renner says he broke 30 bones in snowplow accident
entries.description: "Avengers" star Jeremy Renner says he broke more than 30 bones in the New Year's Day snowplow accident that sent him to the hospital for more than two weeks.

entries.title: Entry to Machu Picchu suspended amid unrest in Peru
entries.description: Tourist entry to Machu Picchu Citadel and the Inca Trail Network has been suspended until further notice due to ongoing unrest in Peru, officials in the country said Saturday.

entries.title: US strike kills approximately 30 al-Shabaab fighters in Somalia
entries.description: The United States carried out a strike in Somalia that killed approximately 30 al-Shabaab fighters, US Africa Command said in a statement Saturday.

entries.title: Discovery in India reveals intimate details about lives of some of the largest dinosaurs
entries.description: To pry open the mysteries of our planet's past, scientists typically study rocks and fossilized bones.

entries.title: Retired astronaut Buzz Aldrin marries 'longtime love' on his 93rd birthday
entries.description: Their wedding must have been out of this world.

entries.title: This butterfly was once thought extinct. Now it's off the endangered species list
entries.description: The Fender's blue butterfly has fluttered away from the brink of extinction.

entries.title: Retailers are tripping over themselves for Millennial and Gen Z shoppers. But not this one
entries.description: Most retailers are tripping over themselves to stay relevant by courting younger Millennial and Gen Z shoppers. Not Lands' End.

entries.title: These old school Hollywood stars are having a moment, and it's long overdue
entries.description: Raise your hand if you are a late bloomer. (I have both hands and feet lifted.)

entries.title: Novak Djokovic overcomes injury to reach Australian Open round of 16
entries.description: Novak Djokovic beat Grigor Dimitrov in straight sets -- 7-6 (9-7) 6-3 6-4 -- to move in the last 16 of the Australian Open, despite a labored performance from the world No. 5 who was visibly struggling to move at points during the match.

entries.title: Andy Murray receives standing ovation from crowd despite Australian Open defeat
entries.description: Andy Murray's fairytale run at the Australian Open came to an end on Saturday after he was beaten by Roberto Bautista Agut.

entries.title: This Lunar New Year, my family will celebrate out loud
entries.description: You could be forgiven if January 22 passes without you noticing anything special about the day. Despite its global significance, most markers of civic society in the US — banks, schools, businesses, and government offices — will bustle with normal activity, oblivious to the most significant cultural and historical holiday for Asian Americans.

entries.title: Why Germany is struggling to stomach the idea of sending tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: The past 12 months has forced European leaders to seriously rethink their approach to national security.

entries.title: Dolphins make a splash in New York City's Bronx River
entries.description: Dolphins are swimming their way back to New York City's Bronx River for the first time in over five years.

Young alligator abandoned in New Jersey heads for new life in Florida
entries.description: A young alligator found in a plastic container in New Jersey has been relocated to another zoo in the state until it is transferred to an alligator sanctuary in Florida.

entries.title: Encounters at sea: Giant squid and great white sharks
entries.description: In travel news this week, China is on the move as the Lunar New Year rush gets underway, a boy makes the catch of a lifetime, temperatures drop to minus 80 F in the world's coldest city, plus what it's like to spend the night in an igloo in the Alps. (Spoiler: It's absolutely freezing).

entries.title: Brazilian soccer star Dani Alves jailed on sexual assault charge by Spanish court
entries.description: Brazilian soccer star Dani Alves, under investigation on a sexual assault charge, was remanded to jail on Friday by a Spanish judge, the Catalonia Higher Court of Justice press office said in a statement.

entries.title: Lucky man from Luck, Wisconsin, wins $15.1 million lottery prize
entries.description: The tiny town of Luck, Wisconsin, is living up to its name, at least for one lucky lottery winner.

Paris Fashion Week: Top moments from the menswear shows
entries.description: The menswear shows in Paris are underway and despite chilling temperatures and a debilitating transit strike, the fashion community is out in full force.

entries.title: Turkey cancels visit by Swedish defense minister after protest permit
entries.description: Turkish Defense Minister Hulusi Akar said on Saturday that a planned visit by his Swedish counterpart to Ankara has been canceled after Swedish authorities granted permission for protests in Stockholm.

entries.title: Indian sports ministry, Olympic Association to investigate sexual harassment allegations against top wrestling official
entries.description: India's sports ministry said Friday it would investigate allegations of sexual harassment against the president of the Wrestling Federation of India (WFI).

entries.title: 'Every week you're a loser.' The brutal world of professional tennis
entries.description: One of the show's stars, Nick Kyrgios, may not have watched it yet, while former world No. 1 Andy Murray says he has no interest in watching it. But Netflix's new fly-on-the-wall documentary 'Break Point' has nevertheless made plenty of headlines since it was released on January 13.

entries.title: 'Rust' will be completed and still star Alec Baldwin as he faces involuntary manslaughter charges in death of crew member, attorney says
entries.description: Alec Baldwin, who is set to face involuntary manslaughter charges in the death of a crew member during a "Rust" film rehearsal, will continue starring as the lead role, a production attorney told CNN on Friday.

entries.title: Two Sydney beaches close, Ironman event abandoned after bull sharks maul dolphin
entries.description: Two popular Sydney beaches were closed Saturday after swimmers witnessed several bull sharks attacking a dolphin, according to Surf Life Saving New South Wales.

entries.title: German indecision on Leopard 2 tanks a 'disappointment:' Ukraine minister
entries.description: Ukraine's Deputy Foreign Minister Andriy Melnyk has expressed frustration in an interview with CNN over Germany's indecision over whether to send its Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine.

entries.title: Pig kills butcher in Hong Kong
entries.description: A butcher died while trying to slaughter a pig in Hong Kong on Friday, the city's police said.

entries.title: Egg shortage sends New Zealanders rushing to buy their own hens
entries.description: Eggs have soared in cost around the world over the past year as avian flu decimated chicken flocks and fallout from Russia's war with Ukraine raised the prices of energy and animal feed.

entries.title: US pilot shot down four Soviet MiGs in 30 minutes -- and kept it a secret for 50 years
entries.description: Royce Williams was a real life "Top Gun" 10 years before Tom Cruise was even born.

entries.title: The Year of the Rabbit: An illustrated guide to Lunar New Year
entries.description: Grab your favorite red shirt; it's time to celebrate the Lunar New Year, also known as Spring Festival.

entries.title: 'If war breaks out, I'm cannon fodder:' In Taiwan, ex-conscripts feel unprepared for potential China conflict
entries.description: Rising concerns over increasingly aggressive military maneuvers by China have prompted Taiwan to extend the mandatory military service period most of its young men must serve. But former conscripts interviewed by CNN say Taipei will need to do far more than that if it is to make the training effective.

entries.title: Video: UFO-shaped cloud shocks residents in Turkish city
entries.description: A UFO-shaped phenomenon called a lens cloud caught the attention of onlookers in Turkey.
